req_add command

    (A) FUNCTION
        Req_add command enables specified facilities to be set
        interactively during simulation with their new values.

    (B) SYNOPSIS

         req_add  { <facility> }

    (C) PARAMETERS
        <facility>
         specifies name of the facility to be requested.

    (D) NOTES
        This requesting functionality is only available when both
        stdin and stderr are associated with interractive terminal.

        On a need of the request, the name facility to be set with a
        value is prompted on the terminal, where the new value to be
        set can be input as a bit string constant.

        EOF (usually ^Z or ^D) may be input when no value should be
        set. In such case value of the facility will be 'z's,
        following the simulation rules of SECONDS.

    (E) SEE ALSO
        req_rmv command
        request command
